#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:85
msgid ""
"This campaign is designed to also work without the War of Legends add-on.\n"
"            \n"
"War of Legends is currently installed which means you will play the version with vampire units from the Era of Myths.\n"
"\n"
"If you want to play the other (lesser) version, uninstall the War of Legends add-on.\n"
"\n"
"Do note, the other version is meant as a 'stopgap' for people who cannot install War of Legends for some reason.\n"
"\n"
"In any case, onto the story!"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:100
msgid ""
"This campaign is designed to also work without the <i>War of Legends</i> add-on.\n"
"            \n"
"It is currently not installed which means you will play the version without vampire units from the Era of Myths.\n"
"\n"
"If you want to play the other (better) version, install the <i>War of Legends</i> add-on.\n"
"\n"
"Do note, this version is meant as a 'stopgap' for people who cannot install War of Legends for some reason.\n"
"\n"
"In any case, onto the story!"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:115
msgid ""
"In the year 253 since the founding of Wesnoth, the kingdom prospered under the rule of Haldric III, King of Wesnoth.\n"
"\n"
"The orcish menace had been beaten back and the lands between Elensefar and Weldyn pacified."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:120
msgid "Since 199YW, colonization of the lands north of the Great River had begun and now, more than fifty years later, thriving settlements had sprung up at the foot of the Heart Mountains and even beyond, in the Far North."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:123
msgid ""
"However, while the rest of the kingdom enjoyed relative peace, this was far from the case in the northernmost reaches where the orcish presence was far greater than further south.\n"
"            \n"
"This, in turn, led to widespread banditry as the army was often occupied repelling orcish incursions."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:128
msgid ""
"The early settlements would not have survived without help from knightly orders who roamed the land, safeguarding vital trade routes and protecting the citizenry from ne'er-do-wells.\n"
"\n"
"Amongst these righteous bands of warriors there were the Knights of the Silver Spire, named for the argent shine of the tower that served as their headquarters within Dorest, the largest city north of the Longlier."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:133
msgid ""
"Their leader was a young knight of the realm who had gone alongside his friends to help make the Northlands safe.\n"
"            \n"
"Though they were relatively new and few in numbers, they had already started to establish themselves as stalwart defenders of the innocent and were tireless in their battles against the enemies of the kingdom."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:140
msgid ""
"It was thus just another day, another patrol on the road towards Lmarig when they learned that the village was being raided by bandits, servants of the Crimson Duke, a new bandit lord that had risen in the region.\n"
"\n"
"They sped with all haste towards the village, hoping to help the villagers and perhaps even find some way to take out the bandits' leader."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:145
msgid ""
"Chapter One\n"
"<i>Just Another Patrol</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:164
msgid "Oh my, ya didn't have that many riches but hey, it's still sum'thing. Tha Crimson Duke'll be happy!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:168
msgid "You pitiful wretch, attacking defenseless civilians!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:172
msgid "Foolish knights, prancing around... Aight boys, pack up the stuff, we're leavin' with da loot!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:176
msgid "Rabble like you should be hanging, not blabbering. Let us rectify this travesty forthwith."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:188
msgid "Fall back, fall ba—!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:198
msgid "The scum is dead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:205
msgid "Scatter the wretches. They will run back to their main camp and we will slaughter them there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:214
msgid "We've got all we could've asked for. Let's lose'em in the mountains!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:218
msgid "No! The villagers won't survive without food!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=02_Bandit_Camp
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:5
msgid "Bandit Camp"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:71
msgid ""
"After the battle, the remains of the bandit force dispersed, trying to head back to safety and their camp.\n"
"\n"
"The knights followed them into the mountains, that they might put an end to this specific threat, once and for all."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:76
msgid ""
"Chapter Two\n"
"<i>Bandit Camp</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:95
msgid "Oh my, more vermin to kill..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:99
msgid "Fools, you led them right here!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:103
msgid "I'll handle 'em master, the Crimson Duke won't be unhappy!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:107
msgid "See that you give him no cause to be displeased."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:120
msgid "That man seemed to be their leader. We must go through them fast and catch him!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:132
msgid "Nooo, master!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:142
msgid "And down he goes... That amount of devotion was unusual, however... Is it because of that <i>Crimson Duke</i> they have as a leader?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:149
msgid "Let us try and catch their <i>master</i> to find out why."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:158
msgid "This is too slow, at this rate he will be lost to us!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=03_Merfolk_Party
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:5
msgid "Merfolk Party"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:98
msgid ""
"The knights hurried after the mysterious figure and attempted to find out who its was.\n"
"            \n"
"However, it proved elusive and its trail was lost north of the mountains."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:103
msgid "This was not all in vain however, for they encountered merfolk battling bandits and dark mages at the source of the River Oumph."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:106
msgid ""
"Chapter Three\n"
"<i>Merfolk Party</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:125
msgid "Hail, noble knights. What brings you here?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:129
msgid "Greetings to you, fair lady. We hunt bandits who have attacked human villages south of here. They have eluded us, though others of their ilk seem to have found their way to you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:133
msgid "Indeed they have, and I would request your aid, for these ones wish to stop us from heading downriver where their brethren are looting an ancient temple hiding dark relics!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:137
msgid "Then we must provide assistance against these miscreants!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:149
msgid "I am sorry... m'lord..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:156
msgid "They were quite dedicated to their superiors."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:160
msgid "Ours were as well, perhaps they are of the same kind. In any case, let us head north as fast as possible."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:169
msgid "At this rate we shall never reach the temple in time!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=04_Temple_Assault
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:5
msgid "Temple Assault"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:98
msgid ""
"After encountering Lady Ariel and her merfolk troops, they all headed north, to the mouth of the river and the temple located there.\n"
"            \n"
"All along, they pondered the motives of these bandits and the reason of their loyalty to the one the caped figure represented, though they believed they would soon obtain the answers."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:103
msgid ""
"Chapter Four\n"
"<i>Temple Assault</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [label]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:124
msgid "Ancient Temple"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:130
msgid "We have arrived. It seems they have already entered the temple!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:134
msgid "In that case, we shall take them out!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL2
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:138
msgid "Enemies are here, protect the master!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BL2
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:150
msgid "Master, we have failed you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:157
msgid "Finally, we shall find out what this is all about."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:166
msgid "They will have stolen everything by the time we get in!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=05_Sacrilege
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:5
msgid "Sacrilege"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:70
msgid ""
"They entered the temple with all haste, that the enemy may be stopped.\n"
"            \n"
"Advancing through these ruins, they felt a chill permeate them, as though a darkness was creeping through."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:75
msgid ""
"Chapter Five\n"
"<i>Sacrilege</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:101
msgid "Wait... You were conniving with the bandits raiding our villages!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:105
msgid "You... You killed quite a few of my master's servants... How annoying..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:109
msgid "What are you doing with these dark relics!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:113
msgid "Taking them with me for the Crimson Duke has need of them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:117
msgid "You shall do no such thing!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:121
msgid "You have no way of stopping me, weakling. Now, do forgive me while I take my leave."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:125
msgid "Return these to their place!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BBH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:138
msgid "Aargh, the Light always hurts... Fools, try and catch me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:150
msgid "That was Baron Luroc, a retainer of Duke Myrraent! We have to arrest him!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=06_Shadows_Rise
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:5
msgid "Shadows Rise"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:22
msgid "Hold until dawn"
msgstr ""

#. [objectives]
#. [objective]: condition=win
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:24
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\misc.cfg:13
msgid "Defeat all enemy leaders"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#. [side]: id=HG, type=General
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:54
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:60
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:74
msgid "Wesnoth"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:90
msgid "Though they tried, they failed to catch Baron Luroc within the temple and, once outside, found no trace of him."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:93
msgid "They were thus left with no recourse but for the knights to head to Farzi, a town within the fiefdom of Duke Myrraent, Luroc's suzerain, in the hopes of informing him of his vassal's conniving with bandits and plundering of forbidden artifacts."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:96
msgid ""
"Chapter Six\n"
"<i>Shadows Rise</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:128
msgid "Hail, we are the Knights of the Silver Spire and we seek an audience with Duke Myrraent on a matter of utmost import."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=SP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:132
msgid "I shall inform him, please come in."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BBH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:166
msgid "My lord Myrraent is not here, might I be of assistance?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:170
msgid "Baron Loruc, traitor to the Crown! We have evidence of your crimes against the realm!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BBH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:174
msgid "I have no time to deal with righteous fools like you. You shall not be tolerated during our rise!"
msgstr ""

#. [modify_side]
#. [side]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:191
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:212
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:74
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:147
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:45
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:50
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:59
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:53
msgid "Vampires"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:219
msgid "I shall enjoy turning you all. Now, let us end this charade."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:223
msgid "Vampires! To battle, everyone! Protect the citizenry and hold until day that we might banish these corpses!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:227
msgid "Tis not for the rabble you should fear."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:294
msgid "What have you done, you monster!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:298
msgid "They have been given a boon they did not deserve that they may better serve our Master."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:308
msgid "This should stem the flow a little..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:320
msgid "No, I will not fall here! You have no chance, the sun will not rise and my minions shall end you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:324
msgid "His hordes are indeed numerous, prepare to withdraw and call upon aid from Dorest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:336
msgid "It should be day by now and yet no sign of the sun..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:340
msgid "I did not pilfer these artifacts without a reason."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:344
msgid "We are being swarmed and there is little room to maneuver... Fall back, we are at a disadvantage in this battle!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:365
msgid "Good, another thrall for our forces."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:369
msgid "I may fall but I am shielded by the Light, I shall never serve your kind!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:384
msgid "Foolish zealots... We won't be able to turn them..."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:5
msgid "Shore of the Avalynne"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:26
msgid "Kill as many enemies as possible before Vaedyr dies"
msgstr ""

#. [objectives]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:28
msgid "Defeat an enemy leader"
msgstr ""

#. [note]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:31
msgid "Losses are irrelevant. The scenario ends when a leader (Vaedyr or an enemy) dies."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:93
msgid "The knights rode for a lightless day, heading southwest towards Dorest to warn of the threat, with the vampires hot on their trail."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:96
msgid "However, they encountered other enemies before the crossing of the Avalynne."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:99
msgid ""
"Chapter Seven\n"
"<i>Shore of the Avalynne</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CDH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:116
msgid "What have we here? Knights running away from someone?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:120
msgid "Duke Myrraent, you arrive at a most opportune time. We were heading to Dorest to warn of Baron Luroc's treachery but it seems this was unnecessary as you may assist us against him!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CDH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:124
msgid "That is a most serious accusation towards one of my vassals. Pray tell, what crime has he commited?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:128
msgid "Not only is he in leagues with the bandits led by the Crimson Duke who have ransacked multiple villages but he is also a vile vampire!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CDH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:132
msgid "Alas, I must decline your request. Knights have always bored me, hunting our kind... And they are so reluctant to obey their betters, unlike common bandits, right, Baron?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:152
msgid "Indeed, sire. The highwaymen proved most amenable, unlike this rabble."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:156
msgid "You are the Crimson Duke? You have been organizing these bandit raids for months!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:160
msgid "Indeed I have, that the kingdom might learn to fear my name. Now submit to superior beings else we shall feast on your blood!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:164
msgid "We are the knights of the Silver Spire and shall never bow to evil! We may be fated to die but we shall not go quietly! Brothers, kill as many as you can, for Wesnoth and for the Light!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:205
msgid "Fight on! Kill... more of... them..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:227
msgid "Foolish humans, they believed they could harm us... How laughable!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:231
msgid "What should we do with them sire, for they cannot be turned easily."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:235
msgid "Kill those who remain then stay here and work on dispelling their protections. Hold the rear guard while I head to Dorest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:252
msgid "You are... but... mortals, this is... impossible!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:256
msgid "Now to his lackey!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:260
msgid "This cannot be happening, fall back to Farzi!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:278
msgid "How, you are but wretched humans!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:286
msgid "Onwards, break them!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:290
msgid "We have not the strength to take Dorest without the artifact, fall back!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=08a_Light_In_The_Dark
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:5
msgid "Light in the Dark"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:32
msgid "Merfolk"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:69
msgid "Though the knights had arrived first, they were not the only one that were heading at the Avalynne."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:72
msgid ""
"Chapter Eight\n"
"<i>Light In The Dark</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:91
msgid "Monsters... I had surmised what you were when we passed Farzi but I still did not truly believe I would find bloodsuckers at the end of the knight's trail."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:95
msgid "Water scum... It seems your hopes were misplaced."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:99
msgid "I shall not let you desecrate their corpses and profane their souls! You will fall to the Light!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:103
msgid "Fools, all of you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:107
msgid "Your fell spells occupy you. You will have no strength for battle and we shall destroy you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:119
msgid "Impossible, we are superior!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:126
msgid "The darkness has receded, now let us banish its remains."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:135
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:95
msgid "I beseech you, o great Light, grant your blessings upon these brave knights who sacrificed themselves against your foes, that they may yet have a chance to save their people."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:157
msgid "Thank you for this hope, it shall not go to waste! (<i>To the other knights</i>) The <i>Crimson Duke</i> is probably heading for Dorest as we speak! We ride with all haste!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:161
msgid "May you succeed in your quest!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$this_item.id
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:169
msgid "What miracle is this!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:178
msgid "That should be enough, they will now rise with us!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=08b_Soothing_Sight
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:5
msgid "Soothing Sight"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:55
msgid ""
"After this hard-won battle, the knights regrouped to prepare to give chase to the vampire forces' remains.\n"
"            \n"
"However, before they could depart, other allies appeared."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:60
msgid "After all, though the knights had arrived first, they were not the only one that were heading upriver."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:63
msgid ""
"Chapter Eight\n"
"<i>Soothing Light</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:83
msgid "Dear knights, I am overjoyed to see you again. When we passed Farzi and saw  signs of battle, I feared the worst."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:87
msgid "I thank you for your concern, fair lady, though happily it was unwarranted, for though we lost many, we routed the enemy. However, I fear not enough of us are left for the next battle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:91
msgid "Left alone, the vampires would still pose a grave threat to all within the North, and the Light shall not allow this to be so."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:113
msgid "Unbelievable! Thank you from the bottom of our hearts, o Lady of Light, for with this boon, we have a chance of ridding the land of these abominations."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:117
msgid "Let it be so. Pray tell, where are their remnants headed?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:128
msgid "The Bloody Baron headed northeast, towards Farzi."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:132
msgid "I had left some of my party there, if we hurry we may yet catch them before they reach their fortress!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:147
msgid "The Crimson Duke headed west, towards the Greenwood."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:151
msgid "Take care, for those who hide within are no friends to other races. Nor are they even to their own."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:155
msgid "I thank you for your warning, I shall take it to heart. Farewell!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=09a_Dawn_over_Dorest
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:5
msgid "Dawn over Dorest"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:99
msgid "The knights sped with all haste towards Dorest, that they might stop the Crimson Duke's evil designs from taking form."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:102
msgid "This was a pressing task for the battle was already fierce in front of the city's walls."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:105
msgid ""
"Chapter Nine\n"
"<i>Dawn over Dorest</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=HG
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:127
msgid "Nooo... The city..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:131
msgid "Finally, this futile resistance is over."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:135
msgid "The city is lost and without it, the North is cut off from Wesnoth, we have failed!"
msgstr ""

#. [label]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:149
msgid "Silver Spire"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=HG
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:155
msgid "Who are you, accursed monster, and why do you trouble our fair city? ...Wait ...Duke Myrraent, is that you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:159
msgid "I have thrown away that fake mask. I am the Crimson Duke and you shall all fall at my feet! Now, despair!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=HG
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:163
msgid "You stand against the kingdom of Wesnoth and have no hope of victory on this day!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:167
msgid "I do not recognize the authority of your pitiful king! You shall all bow down to me!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:171
msgid "Your dark crusade ends here, Crimson Duke!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:175
msgid "The Knights of the Silver Spire... Did I not slay you all?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:179
msgid "The Light does not falter. Your servant is dead and so shall you soon be!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:183
msgid "Go ahead and try, little whelps. The night will soon return and, when it does, you will all die..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:195
msgid "Impossible, deafeated by these wretches!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:199
msgid "Face the wrath of the Light!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:211
msgid "He shall haunt this land no longer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=HG
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:215
msgid "You have our utmost gratitude, oh Knights of the Silver Spire, for you have saved the Northlands and, perhaps, the realm itself from a dark fate."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:232
msgid "How, we slew you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:236
msgid "Begone, foul corpse!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:246
msgid "With the night on my side I am unstoppable! You have no chance!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=09b_Alight_From_All_Sides
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:5
msgid "Alight From All Sides"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:83
msgid ""
"The vampires had suffered a devastating blow with the loss of their leader and were now on the run, fleeing towards their lair at Farzi.\n"
"            \n"
"They hoped to weather the storm headed their way within the walls of the fortified isle."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:88
msgid "They, however, had not expected merfolk to hold them back and keep them from reaching their haven until the knights arrived to finish them off."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:91
msgid ""
"Chapter Nine\n"
"<i>Alight From All Sides</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:110
msgid "Hurry and kill this vermin! We need to reach the island!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:114
msgid "You will not reach safety, vampire. All that awaits you is a final death."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:118
msgid "Foolish mermaid, you face beings far older than you. You are not feared here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:122
msgid "Fear is irrelevant, today you will be eradicated. We, the knights of the Silver Spire, swear so!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:126
msgid "Human scum! Kill them all!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:138
msgid "No... Impossible... Not against wretches like you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:149
msgid "He is dead, we need only finish off the last remains of his despicable ilk. The world will be better off without them. I must thank you for your inestimable assistance against them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:153
msgid "No thanks are necessary, for though he threatened humans now, we would soon have been at risk."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:157
msgid "Well then, I shall have to report this to the lords in Dorest. May we meet again!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:161
msgid "The same to you!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:5
msgid "Death Amongst The Trees"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:22
msgid "Death of the Crimson Duke"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: id=EL, type=Elvish High Lord
#. [side]: id=ES, type=Elvish Sylph
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:67
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:83
msgid "Elves"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:104
msgid "With the death of their Bloody Baron and the destruction of the dark artifact that had been casting a shadow over the battlefield, the nightborn's plans were shattered and they had no choice but to retreat."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:107
msgid "They fled west, towards the Greenwood, without thinking of the cruel beings who dwelled there."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:110
msgid ""
"Chapter Nine\n"
"<i>Death Amongst The Trees</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=EL
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:129
msgid "Fell being, pray tell, what do you seek in these woods but death?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:133
msgid "Nothing from you, foolish elf."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=ES
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:137
msgid "You have stepped within our forest, abomination that was once a man, and for that you shall die."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:141
msgid "Already making new enemies... dear Crimson Duke, perhaps that will be your end."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=EL
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:145
msgid "Humans here! more fools to kill I see..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=ES
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:149
msgid "Let us first handle the monsters, then we shall focus on the beasts."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:161
msgid "No! We were destined for more than this!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:171
msgid "I thank you for the slaying of this monster."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=ES
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:175
msgid "Do not dare speak to me, animal! We rejected your kind and for that were banished! Now you intrude upon our domain and for that you shall pay!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:179
msgid "I am sorry for this state of affair but I have no desire for battle when it is unneeded. (<i>To the knights</i>) Fall back, we retreat!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=10_Epilogue
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:5
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:58
msgid ""
"In the Greenwood, between the shadow of the trees, the three-way battle had now ended with the death of the vampires, their Crimson Duke fallen as if pierced by the very light he had tried to scatter away, all that remained of him a corpse upon the ground, food for worms and no trouble for anyone anymore.\n"
"\n"
"Now the elves faced other foes, for though it had been almost two hundred years since the civil war and their banishment with few left alive from that time, their hatred of mankind still ran deep.\n"
"\n"
"However, today was not to be a day of reckoning, for the human intruders withdrew as fast as possible, seeing no reason to fight a battle they did not want.\n"
"\n"
"On that day, the Knights of the Silver Spire avoided a battle against fellow living beings and, perhaps even planted a seed of doubt within those frozen elven hearts, that perhaps their hatred was unwarranted and that there could be a better way."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:74
msgid ""
"In the darkness a ray of pure light surged forth, piercing through the vampire's heart and breaking his fell artifact.\n"
"        \n"
"As the fell being crumpled, impaled upon a silvery lance, a single ray of sunlight shone upon him as his foul spell broke before the dawn erupted in all its blazing glory, reclaiming its place in the order of things.\n"
"\n"
"And so disappeared the last leader of the vampires much like his liege did the night before, as if to confirm their dark dream's final death and the return of peace to the realm."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:89
msgid ""
"Before the walls of Dorest a great clash had ended. The duel between the knight and the vampire was over with the would-be conqueror struck down by righteous fury, his hordes run down and exterminated.\n"
"                        \n"
"His death brought relief to every soul, for the North was now freed from a grave threat.\n"
"\n"
"The victorious defenders were celebrated for their courage and the Knights of the Silver Spire above all, for all had seen their valor upon the field of battle."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:100
msgid ""
"Vaedyr and his knights reported the events that had transpired to the lords in Dorest, the treachery of Duke Myrraent and his true identity as the Crimson Duke, vampire and would-be subjugator of the North.\n"
"            \n"
"They were justly recompensed for their actions and led a life of virtue afterwards, continuing to act much as they had before, protecting whomever they could."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:105
msgid ""
"Lady Ariel and the merfolk enjoyed years of peace after the incident, untroubled by other threats from the surface and enjoying the benefits of their newfound renown in the form of lucrative trade with the humans.\n"
"    \n"
"Vaedyr and his men oft visited their shores, reminiscing of battles past and assisting whenever the merfolk's diviners foresaw danger."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:110
msgid ""
"Through the bravery of the knights of the Silver Spire, the North, and perhaps all of the continent, were saved from the depredations of the vampire menace.\n"
"            \n"
"Though this did not save the land from future turmoil, their deeds were fondly remembered and soon passed into legend and, like all such tales, were embellished over time."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:123
msgid ""
"Soon, the songs in taverns and stories around the fireplace had forgotten the part the banished elves had played and this became only a tale of the travails of the knights of the Silver Spire, of their desperate stand on the shore of the Avalynne against the Crimson Duke.\n"
"                    \n"
"It told of how, after they had apparently been slain to a man, a maiden of light arose from the water and cried for their fate, bringing about a true miracle.\n"
"\n"
"For before her now stood the entire order, alive and armed, raring to fight once more."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:137
msgid ""
"Soon, the songs in taverns and stories around the fireplace had forgotten the Bloody Baron's flight and was only a tale of the travails of the knights of the Silver Spire, of their desperate stand on the shore of the Avalynne against the Crimson Duke.\n"
"                        \n"
"It told of how, after they had apparently been slain to a man, a maiden of light arose from the water and cried for their fate, bringing about a true miracle.\n"
"    \n"
"For before her now stood the entire order, alive and armed, raring to fight once more."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:152
msgid ""
"Soon, the songs in taverns and stories around the fireplace had forgotten the battles of the merfolk and was only a tale of the travails of the knights of the Silver Spire, of their desperate stand on the shore of the Avalynne against the Crimson Duke.\n"
"                        \n"
"It told of how, after they had been slain to a man, a maiden of light arose from the water and cried for their fate, bringing about a true miracle.\n"
"    \n"
"For before her now stood the entire order, alive and armed, raring to fight once more."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:163
msgid ""
"This tale was known all through Wesnoth and oft told when the bandits of Asheviere were pillaging the countryside or when the hordes of Mal-Ravanal were slaughtering all they could find.\n"
"            \n"
"All who listened knew that this band of knights was long gone and could not ride against the dark this time."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:168
msgid ""
"It still gave hope, however, that someone would.\n"
"            \n"
"That some plucky band of heroes. whether it be a lost prince and his mentor or some guards from the frontier. would fight back and end this new threat, bringing back peace to the realm.\n"
"\n"
"And that hope, that dream that all would be well in the end, well... that was already a wonderful legacy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Grandmaster, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Grandmaster.cfg:7
msgid "Grand Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Grandmaster, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Grandmaster.cfg:23
msgid "Grandmasters are the heads of knightly orders, having shown strength of arms upon the battlefield felling countless threats and a strong will directing their fellow knights. These renowned commanders stand at the front of a righteous charge, inspiring their men to launch another assault when others would have broken already, for the glory of their cause and the hope of a better future."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Horse Lord, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Horse_Lord.cfg:7
msgid "Horse Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Horse Lord, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Horse_Lord.cfg:22
msgid "The greatest of the men of the plains, Horse Lords are heads of their houses and are respected by all, friend or foe. Their sword can kill most ordinary enemies, and their morning star crushes those who are left."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Horseman Commander, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Horseman_Commander.cfg:7
msgid "Horseman Commander"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Horseman Commander, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Horseman_Commander.cfg:28
msgid "Leaders of the border guards, mounted commanders command the garrisons that keep peace in the outermost provinces of Wesnoth. As effective leaders and powerful warriors, these men patrol the countryside and eliminate any and all threats to peace in the frontier villages."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Junior Commander, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Junior_Commander.cfg:7
msgid "Junior Commander"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Junior Commander, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Junior_Commander.cfg:28
msgid "At scarcely 17 or 18 years of age, squires are not yet full knights, but still have the knowledge and skill to master their mounts whilst in full panoply. Talented squires are sometimes given command of small units in Wesnoth’s army, where they gain experience leading fellow troops and honing their prowess in battle."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted Fighter, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_Fighter.cfg:7
msgid "Mounted Fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted Fighter, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_Fighter.cfg:21
msgid "The nobles of the men of the plains are trained with the rest of the horsemen to become great warriors. However, they are also trained in commanding their comrades, and they are the ones that become captains of the armies of the Clans."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted General, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_General.cfg:7
msgid "Mounted General"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted General, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_General.cfg:29
msgid "Switching seamlessly between lance and mace, mounted generals boast tremendous skill in individual combat and can hold their own against even the most powerful opposition. They are masters of their mounts, able to cover great distances quickly on their patrols, and have keen eyes for detecting and eliminating all manner of perilous dangers. Their greatest strength, however, lies in their ability to inspire great courage in their men, who fight fearlessly and tenaciously under their command."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted Warrior, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_Warrior.cfg:7
msgid "Mounted Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted Warrior, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_Warrior.cfg:21
msgid "Leaders of the plains, Mounted Warriors are skilled with the use of the sword and the morning star. Riding horses, they are able to move around the battlefield with great speed, and can provide much needed assistance to different fronts."
msgstr ""

